==English==

===Proper noun===
'''Reuben''' (''plural:'' '''Reubens''')
# A male [[given name]].


===Etymology===
Old Testament Hebrew [[:he:רְאוּבֵ֑ן|רְאוּבֵ֑ן]] (R'uwben), from the imperative of כאשׁר ('ra'ah') and וַתֵּ֣לֶד ('ben'); meaning "see ye a son"; Reuben, a son of Jacob.


